  "body": "[Documentation for ``run``](https://docs.perl6.org/type/IO#sub_run):\r\n> Runs an external command without involving a shell (if possible).\r\n\r\nWhat's the idea behind this “if possible” remark? If it decides to pass your thing to the shell then all of sudden you have a security hole. I don't remember any code for that, so does anybody have any idea what this thing is about?\r\n\r\nAnd also, if it's not covered by roast then let's just delete it.",
